This works with the current service behavior: if the service returns *anything* for this attribute, it will be `true`, otherwise the service throws an exception.
If the service changes behavior in the future and does not throw an exception for non-FIFO queues and does return `true` and `false` values, this code will always return `true`.

The safer approach here is to do this:
```
bool result;
if (bool.TryParse(attributeValue, out result))
    return result;
return false;
```

